    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1267" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπο-λύω</span></b> , aor. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπέλῡσας</span>, subj. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπολύ̄σομεν</span>, mid. fut. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπολῡσόμεθα</span>, aor. part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπολῡσάμενος</span>: I. act., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">loose from, release</span>
          for ransom (Il.): <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἵμαντα θοῶς ἀπέλῡσε
            κορώνης,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Od. 21.46</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> οὐδ᾽
            ἀπέλῡσε θύγατρα καὶ οὐκ ἀπεδέξατ̓ ἄποινα</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 1.95</span></i>.—II. mid., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">loose from
            oneself, get released</span> for oneself, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">ransom;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀπολῡσάμενος</span> (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κρἠδεμνον</span>), <i><span class="en">Od. 5.349</span></i>;
            (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">παῖδας</span>) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χαλκοῦ τε χρῡσοῦ τ᾽ ἀπολῡσόμεθα</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 22.50</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
